Package org.jlab.coda.et.enums

Enum Summary
Age This enum indicates whether an event is a new or unused event, obtained by a call to SystemUse.newEvents(org.jlab.coda.et.Attachment, int, int, int, int), or whether it is an existing or used event, obtained by a call to SystemUse.getEvents(org.jlab.coda.et.Attachment, int, int, int).
DataStatus This enum represents the 3 possible states of an event's data's status.
Mode This enum represents 3 possible modes in which to get new or existing events when no events are currently available (in calls newEvents() or getEvents()).
Modify This enum represents the 3 possible modifications a networked user can make to an event.
Priority This enum represents the 2 possible priorities an event can have.
